title: Japan rain: 3 deaths, levee breaks, many missing
text:
Japan rain: 3 deaths, levee breaks, many missing Original, timely global, travel, tourism, business news and research: 
Sep 11, 2015 eTN Exclusive: Unique and original, timely, global breaking news: 
Osaki City, in the northeastern prefecture of Misaki is the latest victim of extreme weather conditions. At least 100 buildings in the city have been flooded. 
Heavy flooding over eastern Japan has caused three deaths, almost two dozen unaccounted for and houses washed away as residents were forced to their rooftops. Japan's military is part of a major rescue effort. 
Media in the city of Joso, Ibaraki reported the Japanese Self-Defense Force (SDF) helicopters landed on the roof of a shopping center where dozens of people had been stranded overnight. 
Tour operators had been sending updates to overseas clients.
